 a step might be more cost-efficient to perform manually it might get automated in a chain if it sits next to strong AI performers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We characterized and gave efficient algorithms for the firm's short-run and long-run cost minimization problem determining the organization's structure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We showed that returns from marginal improvements in AI quality is not necessarily monotone.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We showed how firms' Leontief production functions can be mapped into a single aggregate CES production function to study macroeconomic implications of AI improvements.
\end_layout

